# ITensor excited states

Finding excited states using the ITensor library
Examples: 1d Ising and 1d Heisenberg model

ITensor - Software Library for Tensor Network Calculations
by Matthew Fishman and Steven R. White and E. Miles Stoudenmire
arxiv.org/abs/2007.14822
http://itensor.org/

Excited states code to large parts by Heitor Peres Casagrande
https://github.com/heitorc7


## Starting guide
(0) Download and build ITensor
http://itensor.org/docs.cgi?vers=cppv3&page=install
git clone https://github.com/ITensor/ITensor itensor
cd itensor
cp options.mk.sample options.mk
Edit options.mk
make

(1) Change path to ITensor
Makefile -> change line 3

(2) Build and execute
cd itensor-excited-states
make
./ExcitedDMRG

(3) Optional: Plot
Run plot.py


## SyTen reference calculations
In SyTen-results there are reference calculations using the SyTen library
by Claudius Hubig, Felix Lachenmaier, Nils-Oliver Linden, Teresa Reinhard, Leo Stenzel, Andreas Swoboda, Martin Grundner and Sam Mardazad
https://syten.eu/

